name: Asbury Memorial United Methodist Church
directions: In sanctuary behind altar

name: Subway
directions: Near the back entrace of the store.

name: Hospital of the University of Pennsylvania
directions: Up the escalators to the right, by the gift shop
comment: You may have to say you’re visiting someone in the hospital but you should be able to say you need to use the restroom

name: Tabu Lounge and Bar
directions: Gender neutral bathrooms can be found downstairs or upstairs on the second floor. Urinals can also be found downstairs

name: Walmart
directions: Back of store by layaway

name: Plymouth State University HUB
directions: Past the mail center and to the right!

name: Center Ice Cafe
directions: Walk in the door, turn to your right and go straight back. Cute sign overhead reads "Penalty Box".
comment: Bathroom is for restaurant customers. But, you can order a latte to go.

name: Visual Arts Center of New Jersey
directions: First floor, on map it is called the Secret Garden.
comment: Feel free to use, also if you turn the lights off -the mosaic glows in the dark.

name: Escape Room Montana
directions: From the lobby, go through the door and stay to your left and its on the left.
comment: Business is appointment only, but owners will show you the restroom.

name: Buzzbrews-Deep Ellum
comment: Unknown if it’s accessible or has changing tables

name: Hello Dumpling
directions: Along right wall behind decorative wall
comment: Don’t recall if there is a changing table but I think there was. Unknown if you need to be a paying customer.

name: Johnson County Community College GEB
directions: Second floor of the GEB building
comment: One of the few single stalls at JCCC. Especially important if you're attending a show at Carlson Center and aren't a student who knows about it.

name: Sam's Club
directions: By Pharmacy
comment: Just tell the door person you are going to the Pharmacy and you will be admitted with no membership card due to company policy

name: Marlow’s Tavern
comment: It’s a restaurant.  They say for customers only, but I doubt they check.

name: Brandon University Library
directions: Second floor

name: Brandon University Health Studies Building
directions: Second floor

name: Unitarian Universalist Fellowship of Falmouth
directions:
Go in the main door and bathrooms are down the hall to your right. Use whichever you wish as the signs indicate. 

A single neutral bathroom is in the parlor to your left upon entry.
comment: The minister is super chill as are the congregants. This is a safe space-- even if you don't need the bathroom.

name: Leslie-Lohman Museum of Gay and Lesbian Art
directions: Admission: suggested donation $9 (as of sept '18). Restroom is in back right of left side gallery from where you enter. Unfortunately can't remember if there's a changing table.
comment: This is an amazing museum! Saw a beautiful photography exhibit of LGBT daily life 1970s-2000s by photographer Donna Gottschalk.

name: Shopton Commons BP
directions: Location is a convenience store. The restrooms are to your right when you enter and are clearly marked. The register is located at the back in the center of the store. There is a single occupancy restroom for women, I assume the men's restroom is the same.
comment: I did not purchase anything inside the store. No one said anything to me upon entering or leaving. I did purchase gas at the pump after using the facilities. I would also like to note, the women's restroom was exceptionally clean.

name: Flying Tiger Copenhagen
directions: Enter store and walk through until you get to back wall. There are two private, un-gendered restrooms. Many inexpensive and fun items in this store!
comment: Not sure if accessible or if changing table is present since I didn't go inside.

name: The Coffee Shop
directions: Back of coffee shop, turn right. 2 different bathrooms.

name: Chance & Counters
directions: Up 2 small sets of 2-3 steps on the left at the back
comment: If you’re not a customer just ask at the bar

name: Walmart
directions: Single occupancy family restroom All the way in the back left of the store by the dairy section
comment: Marked "family restroom" but it's a single occupancy genderless restroom anyone can use. Not uncommon for lone adults to use this restroom

name: Kuma Sushi + Sake
directions: Straight to the back
comment: Small restaurant so you should be a customer. Staff is friendly though and should help you if you don’t feel safe

name: Starbucks
directions: After entering the store restrooms are all the way to the right
comment: Two large, clean single occupancy unisex restrooms with changing tables

name: Stafford cidery
directions: Two bathrooms, both gender neutral

name: Del Taco
directions: Back on the store by the drive thru
comment: Two single occupancy restrooms in back of the store. Both marked "All genders". Need to get token from cashier to get in

name: 926 Bar and Grill
directions:
Pub side: opposite the bar top from the door
Club side: around the corner from the stage or in the back and to the right of the bar
comment: 926 is a “Graight” bar. That welcomes queer people and straight people alike. Not open before 5 all days except for Sunday. Sunday is open at 11 for brunch.

name: Fort Worth Veterinary Specialty & Emergency Hospital
directions: To the left as you enter.
comment: Unkown if they will accommodate non-clients.

name: Sheffield Hallam Students Union - hideout bar
directions: Accessible and gender neural toilet to left of the bar.
comment: Student bar but open to the public most days (unless a special event is on).

name: Laney College Tower Building
directions: 7th floor, take a left from the elevator

name: The Quarry Bisbee
directions: All the way in the back of the restaurant, past the bar. Gendered signs on the door, but both are single toilets with locking doors.
comment: This bar is a safe place/ outspoken left leaning establishment. If you need anything you can alert an employee and they’ll help.

name: Graduate Hotel
directions: First floor, end of hallway past the elevators
comment: This hotel welcomes locals, students, and tourists - you do not have to be a guest.

name: West Oakland BART
directions: Inside the faregates, ground level

name: Brighton memorial library
directions: In the back of the library.  No key. Self locking
comment:
3 single private unisex 
1 is specifically a family bathroom

name: Blue Moon Cafe
directions: In the hallway past the register.
comment: This cafe is owned by a LGBTQ person, very friendly atmosphere

name: Queer Junction
directions: Past the bar

name: Silver Snail Comics
directions: Go up the stairs into the shop. Towards the back on the left are two bathrooms.
comment: Not necessarily for paying customers. As of current (2018) the staff are super queer friendly and won’t question anyone going into the bathroom. Unfortunately not accessible as there are a long set of stairs up. Bathroom doors do have a lock.

name: Lgbtq youth spacd
directions: You’ll see if you go straight back
comment: The space is for youth, so 25 and younger, and they ask that you check in at the front office but I’m sure if you said you need a safe place to go to the restroom it won’t be an issue

name: Panda Express
directions: In back by food pick up

name: Boyd Graduate Research Center
directions: Third floor, right by the elevator on the right-hand side.

name: Newcastle-under-Lyme College
directions: There are several gender neutral and accessible individual toilets scattered around the college.
comment: You have to be a student with your ID card to get into the college.

name: Boys Graduate Research Center
directions: Third floor, right outside of the elevator on the right-hand side.

name: Kool Smiles Dentistry
directions: Behind play area

name: College of San Mateo
comment: All restrooms are safe.   There are single stall restrooms in Bldg 10, 1st floor and Bldg 36, all floors.

name: OCCC
directions: In the hallway between the math and science building, and the main building. There's an exit to the outside right next to it

name: Taste of Belgium
comment: Typically must be a paying customer.

name: Hemp Town Rock
directions: In the back by the change room
comment: No need to be a paying customer, just ask the clerk to use the washroom. Closed Sundays.

name: Walmart
directions: At the back behind to the left of electronics

name: Starbucks
directions: 2 single person restrooms, both unisex

name: Brew Haha!
directions: Restrooms at rear of this coffeehouse.
comment: Men’s room is single-stall style. Unsure about women’s room.

name: Farmer & the Cow
directions: 2 unisex restrooms in rear of restaurant.
comment: Probably intended for customer use only, but during busy periods it may be possible to slip in.

name: Ferris State University Center
directions: Hallway next to TAC, near Starbucks.

name: Idaho River Sports
comment: Extremely friendly to LGBT+.

name: Cedar Ridge Theatre Bathrooms
directions: Enter front doors, head to theatre ramp on the right. Turn right and right once more to go through the dressing rooms and into the bathrooms.
comment:
Since you have to go through a dressing room, for the most part, it’s never full. So there is rarely anyone around that bathroom and should give you a safe space to simply go to the restroom.

Also, smells a lot better than the usual school bathrooms.

name: Farmer & The Cow
directions: 2 unisex restrooms in rear of restaurant.
comment: Presumably you’d need to be a paying customer to use the restroom. If not, you may be able to use during busy/crowded times.

name: Thompson Center
directions: To the left along the wall, keep going and you'll find it.

name: Farmer & The Cow
directions: 2 unisex restrooms in the rear of the restaurant.
comment: Presumably these restrooms are for customers only. If it’s crowded, you may be able to slip in, though.

name: Tate Hall
directions: From West entrance, turn right after entering the main lobby, go towards small corridor, bathroom is on the left in this corridor.
comment: Students make up primary populus in this building, but this bathroom is near the building office, and students rarely spend time in this area. Bathroom and building are open to the public.

name: Latino Cultural Center - Upstairs
directions: Upstairs next to the iTap Computer Lab.

name: Latino Cultural Center
directions: Main floor, on the right after passing the living room area.

name: Kool Smiles Dentistry
directions: Behind the play area
comment: Just ask to use the rr

name: Gordon Oakes Red Bear Student Center
directions: 6 neutral single stalls on upper level, elevator access until 10 pm
comment: anyone respectful and open minded welcome, part of intercultural and indigenous student center.

name: Gordon Oakes Red Bear Student Center- accessible
directions: one on main, another on upper level with elevator access until 10 pm
comment:
anyone respectful and open minded welcome, part of an intercultural and indigenous student center,
no automatic door button, lighter door opening to the inside.

name: Gordon Oakes Red Bear Student Center
directions: six gender neutral single stalls upstairs (elevator access as well)
comment: its an intercultural student center with an indigenous focus. Anyone open minded and respectful is welcome.

name: Crabtree Ale House
directions: Inside the restaurant, restaurant is below the food court
comment: You dont have to be a paying customer, restrooms are gendered, but it is a safe space. Owners and employees are LGBTQAI supportive. Several employees are members of the community and have your back.

name: Starbucks
directions: Both gender neutral restrooms in this Starbucks are single stall and accessible with changing tables.
comment: Purchase not necessary

name: Walmart Neighborhood Market
directions: back by the pharmacy there is a single stall "family" unisex restroom with changing table and locking door

name: Lora campbell
comment: Small bar with awesome inclusive owners and employees. A local haunt for myself and some of my transgenders/non binary pals.

name: Starbucks
directions: The bathrooms are right past the counter.
comment: This particular SB doesn't require you to buy anything, nor do they shoo you for sitting and waiting in the store.

name: Honors College & Residences North
directions: Room 1133 at the front of the advising hallway, first floor
comment: Open to everyone as long as the building is unlocked

name: Fairmont State University
directions: There are 2 gender neutral bathrooms on the second floor of the Library, back in the back corner. If you are disabled you can take the elevator and you’ll come out right by them. There’s another gender neutral restroom in Jaynes hall on the second floor.

name: Meadowbrook Mall
directions: In the food court there is a family restroom you can use. It’s back behind “Tokyo” food court restaurant in the corner there
comment: Family restroom- single stall

name: Stewart Center
directions: If going in through entrance on Memorial Mall, turn left after coming in doors, bathroom is back in a nook to the left of the entrance to Loeb Theater.

name: Starbucks
comment: You have to have bought something and get a receipt with the code
